mode.description: The mode of the level (static-balance or u-turn)

user_locale.description: The language in which instructions are given to the user.

y.description: The y-axis of the accelerometer in G (G=9.81m/s^2). Not collected on android versions older than 8.0 Oreo (API 26)

timestamp.description: The timestamp of the measurement (in ms since the 1st of January 1970 at midnight UTC)

z.description: The z-axis of the accelerometer in G (G=9.81m/s^2). Not collected on android versions older than 8.0 Oreo (API 26)

x.description: The x-axis of the accelerometer in G (G=9.81m/s^2). Not collected on android versions older than 8.0 Oreo (API 26)

file_name.description: The name of the file that contains the instruction or the stimulus that was heard by the user.

start_timestamp.description: The timestamp of the beginning of the voice instruction

y.description: Acceleration along the y-axis due to gravity in G

timestamp.description: The timestamp of the measurement (in ms since the 1st of January 1970 at midnight UTC)

z.description: Acceleration along the z-axis due to gravity in G

x.description: Acceleration along the x-axis due to gravity in G

y.description: The unbiased gyration measured on the y-axis of the device in rad/s (Unbiased Rotation Rate on ios)

timestamp.description: The timestamp of the measurement (in ms since the 1st of January 1970 at midnight UTC)

z.description: The unbiased gyration measured on the z-axis of the device in rad/s (Unbiased Rotation Rate on ios)

x.description: The unbiased gyration measured on the x-axis of the device in rad/s (Unbiased Rotation Rate on ios)

y.description: The y-axis of the accelerometer in G (G=9.81m/s^2), without gravity (User Acceleration on ios, Linear Acceleration on android)

timestamp.description: The timestamp of the measurement (in ms since the 1st of January 1970 at midnight UTC)

z.description: The z-axis of the accelerometer in G (G=9.81m/s^2), without gravity (User Acceleration on ios, Linear Acceleration on android)

x.description: The x-axis of the accelerometer in G (G=9.81m/s^2), without gravity (User Acceleration on ios, Linear Acceleration on android)

y.description: The strength of the calibrated magnetic field along the y direction (from Calibrated Magnetic Field on ios, not collected  on android)

timestamp.description: The timestamp of the measurement (in ms since the 1st of January 1970 at midnight UTC)

z.description: The strength of the calibrated magnetic field along the z direction (from Calibrated Magnetic Field on ios, not collected on android)

x.description: The strength of the calibrated magnetic field along the x direction (from Calibrated Magnetic Field on ios, not collected on android)

y.description: Device orientation roll angle (around y-axis) from Attitude sensor on ios

timestamp.description: The timestamp of the measurement (in ms since the 1st of January 1970 at midnight UTC)

z.description: Device orientation yaw angle (around z-axis) from Attitude sensor on ios

x.description: Device orientation pitch angle (around x-axis) from Attitude sensor on ios

heading.description: Device heading relative to start of activity, calculated by ios CoreMotion. Data is not captured on android and ios < 11

y.description: The strength of the magnetic field along the y direction (from Magnetic Field on ios, not collected on android)

timestamp.description: The timestamp of the measurement (in ms since the 1st of January 1970 at midnight UTC)

z.description: The strength of the magnetic field along the z direction (from Magnetic Field on ios, not collected on android)

x.description: The strength of the magnetic field along the x direction (from Magnetic Field on ios, not collected on android)

y.description: The y-axis of the gyroscope in RPS (Radians Per Second)

x.description: The x-axis of the gyroscope in RPS (Radians Per Second)
